<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Powell</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Port an
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March 22,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Powell reports that he has requested the Haitian Government for an
                            extension of time until May 18 for those Syrians who held false
                            certificates of naturalization, which request has been granted.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>